# How to setup DM
#
# Setup-dm script
# currently only test on Centos6

0. check depends
    depends on bind9, golang, git, ldns, bash, wget
    setup bind9, configure rndc, git repo
    install golang
    install ldns(ldns-verify-zone)
    install wget
    cd bin/
    go build checkns.go
    go build parsednskey.go

1.setting.sh
	configuration for setup DM
    change git repo path
    check depends
    
2.setup-dm.sh
	Yeti root zone generate and publish
    must configure keys when sign Yeti root zone
	sh /path/to/setup-dm.sh

3.manage_root_zone.sh
	add Yeti root name server:
	    sh /path/to/manage_root_zone.sh  add domainname  'IPv6 address'  comment

	delete Yeti root name server:
	    sh /path/to/manage_root_zone.sh  del domainname  comment

	renumbering Yeti root name server:
	    sh /path/to/manage_root_zone.sh  renumbering domainname "new IPv6 address" comment

	update domain of Yeti root name server:
	    sh /path/to/manage_root_zone.sh  updatens domainname "new domain" comment

4.add_crond.sh zsk|ksk
	ZSK/KSK rollover
	sh /path/to/add_crond.sh zsk
	sh /path/to/add_crond.sh ksk

5. Todo
    generate hint file and KSK, upload to github
    add ACLs for Yeti name server zone transfer
    rewrite the program with python/golang
